replyContent:
Hi Albert,

You can copy objects between files by switching to group mode, select the group of objects and use the clipboard icon on the bottom/left side to copy/paste.

Another suggestion would be to be able to delete objects with the X gesture without having to select them first.  Looking forward to future updates.

There is an issue when i wasn't too enter "..." Instead of constantly writing a long list of functions in the class diagram.  Would also love an auto-fit button to resize the shape with a the perfect amount of margin.  The management of the diagram is frustrating if you keep a lot of diagram for references or for large projects. It would be nice if we're can create multiple layers of folders and have both file and folder order by their name, with bookmark listed first as priority.
replyContent:
Hi Luong,

We'll take a look at the auto-resize option.  As for the "..." text, it is actually interpret as multiple bullet indentations by the system because of the markup parser we have.  Right now the work around if you really need to show "..." in a new line is use .h. tag in front of it first.

replyContent: The current canvas size is 6144 x 6144.  There is a big difference in memory between the desktop and mobile devices that we have to put some limit.  We can double it by raising the canvas limit to 10240 x 10240 in the future .  To make it truly unlimited we have to reevaluate some of the older devices we are currently supporting.

content: Been waiting for a decent flowcharting app for ages. This trounces the competition hand down. Sarted with the free version and thn updated to the paid one asap. Excellent gesture based ui. Bought after a day of using the lite version. As always a couple of features would be nice, but I understand what it takes to impliment changes: Fully integrate with google drive? Add images from gallery/folder? Change border and text colour (would also allow for text on its own - clear border) also change shape option at later date without redrawing? This an elegant app for diagramming. I am a modeler/researcher and use this app daily to prototype complex decision models. It works very well and despite its simplicity is amazingly powerful.
